# Pinakes scheduled tasks — run by supercronic inside the container.
#
# Docker images have no cron daemon, so without this the automatic
# notification emails and nightly maintenance never run. supercronic reads
# this file and fires the jobs on schedule (see docker-entrypoint.sh).
#
# Times are in the CONTAINER's timezone (UTC unless you set TZ in your
# compose/env). Set TZ to your library's local time so the "opening hours"
# window below lines up with reality. This mirrors the bare-metal crontab
# documented in the Pinakes README.
#
# Standard 5-field cron:  minute hour day-of-month month day-of-week  command
#
# Hourly, 08:00–20:00 — send due-soon and overdue loan notification emails.
0 8-20 * * * /usr/local/bin/php /var/www/html/cron/automatic-notifications.php
#
# Daily at 06:00 — full maintenance: loan state transitions (mark overdue),
# reservation/pickup expiry, notifications, ICS calendar regeneration.
0 6 * * * /usr/local/bin/php /var/www/html/cron/full-maintenance.php
